Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in oven safe skillet over high heat. Pat tuna dry, season and add to pan. Cook 2 minutes per side. Place skillet in oven 12-14 minutes, until steaks are cooked through. Toss orzo with 2 tablespoons olive oil, bruschetta topping, tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Place orzo on each plate and top with tuna steak. Serve with lemon wedges.